From: Samuel Thibault <samuel.thibault@ens-lyon.org>
Subject: [PATCH] Add more ipv6 macros.

http://www.sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=3906

“bits/in.h #defines IPV6_RXINFO 2, while sysdeps/unix/sysv/linux/bits/in.h
defines IPV6_PKTINFO (and no RXINFO). For better compatibility, shouldn't
IPV6_RXINFO be deprecated and IPV6_PKTINFO defined as a replacement?”

2007-01-23  Samuel Thibault  <samuel.thibault@ens-lyon.org>

	* bits/in.h (IPV6_PKTINFO): Define new macro.
	(IPV6_RXINFO,IPV6_TXINFO,SCM_SRCINFO): Redefine to IPV6_PKTINFO.
